        was presented in class. Our collective agreement was that to ensure
        value in the check-in service, we had to ask where the service could
        fail. While the team and I (and our classmates) could imagine multiple
        points where such an event could happen, I felt that working on the
        first step, where Canada Post would have to establish trust between the
        service and the customer, was the most actionable step in a designer's
        context.
      </p>
