      <h4>Four fundamental pillars for enabling "Aging in the Right Place"</h4>
      <p>
        Secondary research sourced from the <a
          href="https://www.niageing.ca/"
          target="_blank">National Institute of Ageing (NIA)</a
        > - particularly, their <a
          href="https://www.niageing.ca/airp"
          target="_blank">"Ageing in the Right Place" report</a
        >, defines four fundamental pillars that are essential in enabling older
        adults to age in the most appropriate setting where their personal
        preferences, circumstances, and care needs are met.

        <br /><br />
        This framework helped my team and I scope down our service focus to the fourth
        pillar,
        <strong
          >improving social connections to reduce loneliness and social
          isolation</strong
        >. I felt that this focus would be essential in keeping the trust of
        Carriers that Care, as I feel that postal workers would not have the
        capacity to reasonably support the other three pillars without
        fundamental changes to their jobs.
      </p>
    </div>
